# Development Tools

## Testing

### Unit Tests

- Unit tests for helpers, composables, or components in isolation.
- Co-locate with file under test: `[NameOfComponent].unit.spec.js`.
- Use `@vue/test-utils`.
- Quality over quantity.

### E2E Tests

- Add `data-testid` to all interactive elements (buttons, links, inputs, selects, modals, toggles).
- Format: `data-testid="<context>-<element>"` e.g. `data-testid="login-submit-btn"`, `data-testid="sidebar-nav-dashboard"`, `data-testid="login-email-input"`.
- `data-testid` must be stable and not derived from dynamic content (no IDs, indices, or user-generated strings).
- E2E tests live in `e2e/`. Use Playwright selectors via `getByTestId()`.

## Node / JS / TypeScript

- Use npm for package management.

## Typing and Linting

- Prettier for formatting.
- Do not use type `any`.
